rComments: I took Philosophy of Sexuality with Prof Serchuk during the summer. He is passionate about the subject and he tries his best to each the class to analyze the material in a philosophically rigorous way. He is also pleasant to chat with after class.

I liked this professor because it seemed like he enjoyed engaging the class. I liked that he had a discussion forum. I found him to be a bit opinionated at times, which could undermine his philosophical approach. Nonetheless, I thought he was a great professor. A class with him is a worthwhile experience.
Prof. Serchuk is one of the best professors I've ever had. Hilarious, concise, intelligent, engaging. It's a difficult course but ever-so-enjoyable!

Dr. Serchuk is probably the greatest prof I've ever had but man this is one dirty course! He takes extremely challenging material and presents it in a fun and relatively nonthreatening way. Even when people asked stupid questions he was patient and respectful.

Fun lectures, but not the exams! Exam difficulty was not very high, but there was a general lack of time on all exams and it felt like being tested on speed, not knowledge and understanding.It is a logic course after all.He has the potential to be great once he learns how to truly measure his students' knowledge.Sorry for the guniea pigs meanwhile.
The course is crazy hard but he is a pretty fun prof. Played some ridiculous video before the test to ease the tension.. it worked but I still failed QQ He does give lots of bonus marks which is nice
